1
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:42,833
<i>I won't let you
destroy my family!</i>

2
00:00:42,967 --> 00:00:44,500
<i> I will fight that woman!</i>

3
00:00:44,633 --> 00:00:45,300
<i> Let go of me!</i>

4
00:00:45,433 --> 00:00:46,433
<i> I won't!</i>

5
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:50,000
<i> Jessica!</i>

6
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,633
<i> Jessica!</i>

7
00:00:51,767 --> 00:00:52,867
<i> Mom.</i>

8
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,100
<i> I'm right here, Andrea.</i>

9
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:56,167
<i>I don't want you
to get hurt, Mom.</i>

10
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:57,333
<i> Let me go!</i>

11
00:00:57,467 --> 00:00:58,833
<i>Why are you putting me in jail?</i>

12
00:00:58,967 --> 00:01:00,000
<i> My daughter needs me!</i>

13
00:01:00,133 --> 00:01:01,533
<i> Let me out of here!</i>

14
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:02,633
<i> Andrea!</i>

15
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:06,733
<i> Jessica!</i>

16
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:08,300
<i>Jessica! Call the doctor!
Jessica!</i>

17
00:01:08,433 --> 00:01:09,067
<i> Who are you?</i>

18
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:11,667
<i> What did you do to her?</i>

19
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:13,833
<i> Wait a minute!</i>

20
00:01:13,967 --> 00:01:15,300
<i> Why am I wearing this?</i>

21
00:01:15,433 --> 00:01:17,267
<i> You bastard!</i>

22
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:35,267
<i> Thank you for everything.</i>

23
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:39,633
<i>We're very sorry for all
the trouble we've caused you.</i>

24
00:01:39,767 --> 00:01:41,267
<i> Dad is right.</i>

25
00:01:41,433 --> 00:01:43,267
<i> You're incredibly kind.</i>

26
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:47,600
<i>I'm the product of my parents'
wrongdoing,</i>

27
00:01:47,733 --> 00:01:51,767
<i>and yet, you're still
so kind to me.</i>

28
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:54,767
<i> You never made me feel hated.</i>

29
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:26,600
My God.

30
00:02:26,733 --> 00:02:28,200
Please don't leave me, Sweetie.

31
00:02:36,533 --> 00:02:38,100
- You!
- Wait!

32
00:02:38,233 --> 00:02:39,167
Listen to me!

33
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,267
Jesus! Joel!

34
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,633
- What's going on here?
- Listen to me first!

35
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:42,333
What is this?

36
00:02:42,467 --> 00:02:43,933
I'm glad you're here!

37
00:02:44,067 --> 00:02:47,833
I'm just bringing this medicine
for your friend's hangover.

38
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,100
What's going on?

39
00:02:49,233 --> 00:02:51,000
Who is he?

40
00:02:51,133 --> 00:02:52,567
This is Belen.

41
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:54,633
She's one of my tenants.

42
00:02:54,767 --> 00:02:57,300
I called her
and asked her a favor

43
00:02:57,433 --> 00:02:59,100
to give Andrea a sponge bath.

44
00:02:59,233 --> 00:03:00,200
That's right, Andrea.

45
00:03:00,333 --> 00:03:01,567
I cleaned you up.

46
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:16,467
Bro, I'm sorry. I thought...

47
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,933
I understand.

48
00:03:18,067 --> 00:03:20,533
My name is Joel, by the way.

49
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:23,400
He's my landlord, Jeff.

50
00:03:25,433 --> 00:03:28,167
I'm Jeffrey, Andrea's brother.

51
00:03:32,867 --> 00:03:33,833
Are we good now?

52
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:36,933
We're going to head out now.

53
00:03:37,067 --> 00:03:39,067
Okay. I'm sorry, Bro.

54
00:03:39,200 --> 00:03:40,067
- I'm sorry, too.
- It's okay.

55
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,633
Thank you.

56
00:03:41,767 --> 00:03:43,033
Your shirt.

57
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:54,267
Jeffrey...

58
00:03:54,433 --> 00:03:57,433
Why are you suddenly
barging in here?

59
00:03:57,567 --> 00:04:00,400
I gave you a keycard
for emergencies,

60
00:04:00,533 --> 00:04:03,533
not so you could cause a scene.

61
00:04:03,667 --> 00:04:06,033
What's the matter?
Why are you here?

62
00:04:06,167 --> 00:04:07,600
I've been trying to call you,
but you're not answering.

63
00:04:07,733 --> 00:04:09,033
Isn't that an emergency?

64
00:04:09,167 --> 00:04:11,600
Why did you drink with that guy?

65
00:04:11,733 --> 00:04:13,667
I was in a bad mood.

66
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:19,067
Because mom and Coleen threw
a birthday party for Jessica.

67
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:21,367
Why are you calling?

68
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:25,500
I was just going to tell you
that Hazel caused trouble again.

69
00:04:25,633 --> 00:04:26,567
What?

70
00:04:26,700 --> 00:04:28,433
And then, she ended up
hurting her daughter.

71
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:30,500
Your father's daughter.

72
00:04:30,633 --> 00:04:33,033
She's in the hospital right now.

73
00:04:33,167 --> 00:04:34,133
What about mom?

74
00:04:34,267 --> 00:04:35,300
She's fine.

75
00:04:35,433 --> 00:04:37,767
Mom and Coleen are fine.
It's Jessica who got hurt.

76
00:04:37,900 --> 00:04:41,433
So she would hurt her
own daughter, too.

77
00:04:41,567 --> 00:04:43,867
Maybe what your dad said
is true,

78
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,733
that they were being abused
by that woman.

79
00:04:47,867 --> 00:04:49,533
So she's really that bad.

80
00:04:49,667 --> 00:04:53,233
If you saw her,
her eyes were glaring.

81
00:04:53,367 --> 00:04:54,900
She honestly looked
like a demon.

82
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,600
You haven't seen her yet, right?

83
00:04:58,733 --> 00:05:00,867
I have no intention
of seeing her.

84
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:03,700
She should be grateful
she didn't hurt mom.

85
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:05,100
Because if she did...

86
00:05:05,533 --> 00:05:09,500
There she goes again.
So dramatic!

87
00:05:09,633 --> 00:05:13,800
But you know what,
I thought the same thing.

88
00:05:13,933 --> 00:05:15,467
I was worried about mom.

89
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,533
She's my priority.

90
00:05:16,667 --> 00:05:17,767
That's what you
get for drinking.

91
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,833
Lie down. Lie down!

92
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:20,933
Put this on your head.

93
00:05:24,033 --> 00:05:27,333
That's what you get.

94
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:29,333
It's natural to worry about her.

95
00:05:29,467 --> 00:05:31,600
Because we're good kids.

96
00:05:31,733 --> 00:05:33,567
We're responsible.

97
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:37,433
We should get an award
for being such good children.

98
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,433
Best child award.

99
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:43,367
Hey, listen to me.

100
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:46,500
Don't ever drink without me.

101
00:05:46,633 --> 00:05:48,900
Hey, Andrea, listen to me.

102
00:05:49,033 --> 00:05:51,767
Because if I ever see
someone disrespecting you,

103
00:05:51,900 --> 00:05:54,033
Daisy might end up a widow.

104
00:05:54,167 --> 00:05:55,500
I'm telling you.

105
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:57,833
What? I don't get it.

106
00:05:57,967 --> 00:06:01,500
If someone takes advantage
of you,

107
00:06:01,633 --> 00:06:03,733
I will kill that person.

108
00:06:03,867 --> 00:06:05,033
Then Daisy will end up a widow.

109
00:06:05,167 --> 00:06:06,300
Dumbass.

110
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:11,200
How will she end up a widow
when you're not married?

111
00:06:11,367 --> 00:06:13,067
I know why your head hurts!

112
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:16,200
- Ouch!
- Here's the remedy.

113
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:17,500
This is what happened.

114
00:06:17,633 --> 00:06:23,333
Your daughter's electrolytes
drop due to excessive vomiting.

115
00:06:23,467 --> 00:06:26,433
How is she doing now?

116
00:06:26,567 --> 00:06:31,100
Although the swelling
in the brain has decreased,

117
00:06:31,233 --> 00:06:33,433
contusions are still present.

118
00:06:33,567 --> 00:06:37,100
She is in a transient coma
right now.

119
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:40,633
A temporary type of coma.

120
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:43,167
She's responding to stimulus.

121
00:06:43,300 --> 00:06:46,900
Spontaneous eye opening,
verbal output,

122
00:06:47,033 --> 00:06:48,667
and muscular movement.

123
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:51,633
That's good news, right?

124
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:52,700
Well, yes.

125
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:57,233
But still, this 24 to 48 hours
are critical.

126
00:06:57,367 --> 00:06:59,800
Jessica has to wake up around
that time

127
00:06:59,933 --> 00:07:04,333
to check if her condition
is getting better.

128
00:07:04,467 --> 00:07:06,167
- Okay, I have to go.
- Thank you.

129
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:08,100
- Thank you, Doc.
- Thank you, Doc.

130
00:07:12,867 --> 00:07:14,167
It's Jessica's birthday,

131
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:18,200
and this is what happened
to her.

132
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:21,833
We just want to make her happy.

133
00:07:21,967 --> 00:07:25,167
And she ends up like this.

134
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:28,367
What if she never wakes up?

135
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:32,167
Manuel, don't think like that.

136
00:07:32,300 --> 00:07:34,067
Your daughter will wake up.

137
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:35,167
She will get better.

138
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:40,133
Bro...

139
00:07:40,267 --> 00:07:42,133
I think it's better
if we go home for now

140
00:07:42,267 --> 00:07:43,967
so we can get some rest.

141
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:46,867
And then we can pray to God
that she'll soon wake up.

142
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:48,833
I'm staying here, Bro.

143
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,033
I'm going to stay by her side.

144
00:07:50,167 --> 00:07:51,400
I want her to see me
when she wakes up.

145
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:52,700
I can't leave her.

146
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:54,300
Okay, okay.

147
00:07:54,567 --> 00:07:55,700
I'll stay with you.

148
00:07:58,367 --> 00:08:03,633
Abel, Paz, can you drop
Coleen off at home?

149
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:07,433
Okay, Mom.

150
00:08:07,567 --> 00:08:10,400
I will ask Didang to bring you
clothes tomorrow morning.

151
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:11,833
Okay, Sweetie. Thank you.

152
00:08:14,900 --> 00:08:16,833
- Friend?
- What?

153
00:08:16,967 --> 00:08:19,167
Are you sure about this?

154
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:23,167
Do you really have to stay here
with Manuel?

155
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:24,967
Abel can stay here with him.

156
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:27,733
Other people might get
a wrong impression,

157
00:08:27,867 --> 00:08:29,800
you know what I mean?

158
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:36,733
Are you one of those
malicious people?

159
00:08:36,867 --> 00:08:38,833
I don't think like that.

160
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:41,500
But I can't help
but notice, you know?

161
00:08:41,633 --> 00:08:44,833
The way you and your ex
are acting...

162
00:08:44,967 --> 00:08:47,767
It's kind of giving
in-a-relationship vibe,

163
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:48,933
don't you think?

164
00:08:50,533 --> 00:08:51,867
Friend.

165
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,033
We're just friends.

166
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,233
Don't think like that.

167
00:08:56,367 --> 00:08:59,300
It's just that,
maybe it's not clear to you

168
00:08:59,433 --> 00:09:02,067
where that friendship
of yours is heading.

169
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:05,300
Remember, he's still married.

170
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:07,467
Thanks.

171
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,967
But you don't need to remind me.

172
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:11,967
I know my place.

173
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:15,000
Okay, we'll head home then.

174
00:09:15,133 --> 00:09:16,467
Okay, take care.

175
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:24,167
We'll drop her off.

176
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:26,700
Let's go, Sweetie.

177
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:29,533
- Bro, we'll get going.
- Mother. Bye.

178
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:30,633
Thank you.

179
00:09:30,767 --> 00:09:32,133
Bro.

180
00:09:32,267 --> 00:09:33,867
Okay.

181
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:34,900
Thank you.

182
00:09:58,567 --> 00:10:01,400
There shouldn't be
a weekend break.

183
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:04,733
You should serve 24/7.

184
00:10:04,867 --> 00:10:07,900
You should have let me out
the moment I made bail.

185
00:10:08,033 --> 00:10:11,333
Mrs. Cruz, please be quiet.

186
00:10:11,467 --> 00:10:13,133
I'm just stating facts.

187
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:17,400
I wasted my time here.

188
00:10:17,533 --> 00:10:19,367
I didn't get any sleep!

189
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:21,367
Never in my wildest imagination

190
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,400
would I stay in prison
for that long!

191
00:10:25,133 --> 00:10:27,133
I didn't get any sleep
worrying about my daughter.

192
00:10:28,300 --> 00:10:29,867
I'm a nurse, I'm a mom,

193
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:32,200
but I couldn't get
to my daughter.

194
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:34,767
That's enough, Bestie.

195
00:10:34,933 --> 00:10:37,333
You should go see Jessica.

196
00:10:49,767 --> 00:10:51,833
Miss.

197
00:10:51,967 --> 00:10:53,967
Which room is
Jessica Capistrano Cruz in?

198
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:55,933
She was brought here yesterday.

199
00:10:56,067 --> 00:10:58,633
I'm her mother,
Hazel Capistrano-Cruz.

200
00:10:58,767 --> 00:11:00,000
She's in the ICU.

201
00:11:00,133 --> 00:11:00,733
Third floor.

202
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,467
ICU.

203
00:11:13,167 --> 00:11:14,333
Alice, can you hold this...

204
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:25,067
Don't you dare get
near my daughter!

205
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,767
What do you expect?

206
00:11:26,900 --> 00:11:31,500
I wouldn't be able to make
bail to see my daughter?

207
00:11:31,633 --> 00:11:34,267
You can't stop me, Manuel.

208
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:37,267
I have a right,
Jessica is my daughter.

209
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:38,700
Yes! And you hurt her!

210
00:11:38,833 --> 00:11:39,867
I didn't mean to hurt her!

211
00:11:43,567 --> 00:11:45,500
She's the reason why she's hurt.

212
00:11:45,633 --> 00:11:46,667
It's that woman's fault!

213
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:49,500
She's the reason
why Jessica got hurt.

214
00:11:49,633 --> 00:11:53,100
Don't blame me for what
you've done to your daughter.

215
00:11:53,233 --> 00:11:56,600
Hazel, can you please leave?

216
00:11:56,733 --> 00:11:59,600
You have such a thick hide!

217
00:11:59,733 --> 00:12:03,400
You're asking me to leave?

218
00:12:03,533 --> 00:12:05,367
Jessica is my daughter.

219
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:07,533
I'm her mom, so I won't
leave this place

220
00:12:07,667 --> 00:12:08,967
until I see my daughter!

221
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:10,167
No.

222
00:12:10,300 --> 00:12:12,700
I can't let my daughter see
the person who hurt her!

223
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:14,267
Go on, Hazel!

224
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,133
Leave!

225
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:19,833
And if I don't, what are you
going to do, Manuel?

226
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:22,333
You'll drag me out of here?

227
00:12:22,467 --> 00:12:25,000
Can you handle me?

228
00:12:25,133 --> 00:12:25,900
Hazel!

229
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:26,900
- Let me go!
- Enough.

230
00:12:27,033 --> 00:12:27,833
- Hazel, you have to leave!
- Let me go!

231
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:31,800
I need to see my daughter!

232
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:33,967
I said, leave!

233
00:12:34,100 --> 00:12:35,133
Leave us alone!

234
00:12:35,267 --> 00:12:36,400
- Hazel!
- Let me go, Manuel!

235
00:12:36,533 --> 00:12:37,733
Hazel! Go on!

236
00:12:37,867 --> 00:12:38,933
- You have to leave.
- I need to see Jessica!

237
00:12:39,067 --> 00:12:41,100
- Don't make a scene here!
- What's happening here?.

238
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:42,767
- Guard!
- Guard...

239
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:44,433
- Guard, please help me.
- Make her leave.

240
00:12:44,567 --> 00:12:45,400
- No, no!
- She's the reason

241
00:12:45,533 --> 00:12:47,133
why my daughter is in the ICU.

242
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:48,467
Guard, listen to me.

243
00:12:48,633 --> 00:12:49,833
- Let's go, Ma'am.
- Wait, please help me.

244
00:12:49,967 --> 00:12:50,767
No, he's my husband.

245
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:51,700
And that's his mistress!

246
00:12:51,833 --> 00:12:52,767
They didn't want me
to go in there.

247
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:53,867
I just want to see my daughter.

248
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,567
You have to leave, Ma'am.

249
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:55,500
No, I'm not leaving.

250
00:12:55,633 --> 00:12:57,100
Make her leave.

251
00:12:57,233 --> 00:12:58,600
I filed a complaint against her.

252
00:12:58,733 --> 00:12:59,933
Get her out of here.

253
00:13:00,067 --> 00:13:01,767
-Manuel you can't do this to me!
-She might do something drastic.

254
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,367
- Go on! Please!
- Jessica!

255
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:04,233
Please, guard.

256
00:13:04,367 --> 00:13:06,100
I need to see Jessica.

257
00:13:11,733 --> 00:13:13,367
Where's Hazel?

258
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:14,633
Where is she?

259
00:13:14,767 --> 00:13:16,133
Alice.

260
00:13:16,267 --> 00:13:17,133
Hazel.

261
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:19,067
Why did you leave me there?

262
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:21,133
I had to hide from Felma.

263
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,433
If she sees me, you wouldn't
have a spy at FMP.

264
00:13:26,133 --> 00:13:27,933
They wouldn't let me see
Jessica.

265
00:13:29,933 --> 00:13:34,567
I'm her mother,
but Felma's the one in there!

266
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:36,933
I don't know what's going on
with my daughter.

267
00:13:37,067 --> 00:13:38,833
She's in the ICU.

268
00:13:38,967 --> 00:13:40,867
I don't know what the
doctor's findings are.

269
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:44,267
She could have
internal bleeding,

270
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:48,667
or worse, a fractured skull.

271
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:51,067
She could have an internal
organ damaged

272
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:53,667
that they haven't detected yet,
I don't know.

273
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:56,167
What if they're overloaded
with patients

274
00:13:56,333 --> 00:14:00,500
and couldn't tend
to my daughter?

275
00:14:00,633 --> 00:14:01,933
I'm a nurse.

276
00:14:02,067 --> 00:14:04,967
I can take care of my daughter.

277
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:07,267
I should be in there.

278
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:09,500
We can't blame Manuel.

279
00:14:09,633 --> 00:14:12,867
You're the reason
why Jessica got hurt.

280
00:14:16,633 --> 00:14:18,833
That accident wouldn't
have happened

281
00:14:18,967 --> 00:14:22,200
if Felma hadn't been
trying to play the hero.

282
00:14:22,333 --> 00:14:24,500
She's taking my place
as Jessica's mother.

283
00:14:27,467 --> 00:14:29,933
That should've been me.

284
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:32,300
Just a reminder.

285
00:14:32,433 --> 00:14:36,167
Aside from the trespassing
and public scandal

286
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:38,567
complaint filed by the
restaurant manager,

287
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:42,133
you also have a serious physical
injuries complaint from Manuel.

288
00:14:42,267 --> 00:14:43,567
Don't provoke him further.

289
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:45,833
He might add to his complaint.

290
00:14:45,967 --> 00:14:50,633
Come on, let's go to church
and pray for Jessica.

291
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,733
What are you waiting for?

292
00:14:59,867 --> 00:15:01,500
Get in the car.

293
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:02,800
I have to see my daughter.

294
00:15:05,133 --> 00:15:06,633
I need to go to Jessica.

295
00:15:06,767 --> 00:15:07,967
I need to get near her.

296
00:15:10,167 --> 00:15:12,633
Hazel! What are you going
to do now?

297
00:15:15,533 --> 00:15:16,400
Your clothes look good.

298
00:15:16,533 --> 00:15:17,867
It's all neatly pressed.

299
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:20,300
Did you finish your homework?

300
00:15:20,433 --> 00:15:21,533
Wait a minute,
let me fix your collar.

301
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,533
Do you have your lunch box?

302
00:15:25,667 --> 00:15:26,667
- Daddy.
- Yeah?

303
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:29,700
Mom told me that you had
a fist fight

304
00:15:29,833 --> 00:15:31,400
with Aunt Andrea's friend.

305
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:36,167
Daisy, you shouldn't be
telling Tetay things like that.

306
00:15:37,967 --> 00:15:39,000
No, Sweetie, it was nothing.

307
00:15:39,133 --> 00:15:41,467
Just a misunderstanding,
but we've already cleared it up.

308
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:42,667
Don't worry about it, okay?

309
00:15:45,433 --> 00:15:47,967
Jeff, Coleen called.

310
00:15:48,100 --> 00:15:49,967
She said Jessica's
still unconscious.

311
00:15:56,767 --> 00:15:58,067
Jeff?

312
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,467
There's nothing I can do
about that.

313
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:02,633
I'm not a doctor.

314
00:16:04,767 --> 00:16:06,567
But I hope she'll wake up.

315
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:16,100
Bro, what's up?

316
00:16:19,067 --> 00:16:21,700
Of course, I will be there

317
00:16:21,833 --> 00:16:24,867
after I drop Tetay
off at school.

318
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:25,500
Okay.

319
00:16:25,633 --> 00:16:26,633
Thanks, Bro.

320
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,467
Who's that?

321
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:31,733
It's Pablo.

322
00:16:31,867 --> 00:16:34,200
Well, he said he recommended me
at the factory where he works.

323
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:35,167
Really, Dad?

324
00:16:35,300 --> 00:16:36,400
You got a job again?

325
00:16:36,533 --> 00:16:37,433
That's right!

326
00:16:37,567 --> 00:16:41,600
I can buy whatever you want
again!

327
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:43,733
High five!

328
00:16:43,867 --> 00:16:46,200
Eat up.

329
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:47,333
I'm sorry about my brother.

330
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:51,700
He's protective of me.

331
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:54,267
A little too much sometimes.

332
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:57,167
No problem, I understand.

333
00:16:57,300 --> 00:16:59,300
You don't need to do
this peace offering.

334
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,033
How are you?

335
00:17:03,167 --> 00:17:05,233
Are you still mad at your mom?

336
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:08,167
This won't be resolved.

337
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:11,267
Not until she stops letting her
ex stay in her house.

338
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:15,000
I hope you and your mom
patch things up.

339
00:17:16,567 --> 00:17:19,533
You're lucky to have a mom.

340
00:17:23,467 --> 00:17:24,800
It's hard not having a mother.

341
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:30,767
Sorry, Andrea.

342
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:36,067
I didn't mean to intervene.

343
00:17:37,600 --> 00:17:40,733
It's okay, let's eat.

344
00:17:40,867 --> 00:17:43,633
I have an interview at 11:00 AM.

345
00:17:43,767 --> 00:17:45,400
Thanks again.

346
00:17:45,533 --> 00:17:46,400
This is good.

347
00:17:51,667 --> 00:17:55,233
Sweetie, can you hear me?

348
00:17:57,633 --> 00:18:01,400
Too bad your birthday
had to be cut short.

349
00:18:04,667 --> 00:18:06,233
It's your mom's fault.

350
00:18:09,233 --> 00:18:10,233
Sweetie...

351
00:18:12,067 --> 00:18:15,067
I know that you'll wake up.

352
00:18:15,200 --> 00:18:16,733
You will get through this.

353
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:19,233
But, Sweetie...

354
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:22,700
can you wake up now, please?

355
00:18:26,033 --> 00:18:28,500
Because I'm getting worried.

356
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:37,933
Please, wake up.

357
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:41,867
<i> Sweetie!</i>

358
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:42,700
<i> Andrea!</i>

359
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:43,600
<i> Nurse!</i>

360
00:18:43,733 --> 00:18:44,667
<i> Nurse! Please help!</i>

361
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:47,033
<i> Andrea can't breathe!</i>

362
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:48,933
<i> What's happening to her?</i>

363
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,700
<i> Please help my daughter!</i>

364
00:18:52,833 --> 00:18:53,700
<i>- Help her.
- We will,</i>

365
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:54,967
<i> we'll take care of her.</i>

366
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:14,000
<i> Andrea, sweetie.</i>

367
00:19:14,133 --> 00:19:15,100
<i> How are you?</i>

368
00:19:29,867 --> 00:19:34,567
Jessica, I know
how your father feels.

369
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:38,967
I felt the same way
when Andrea was in the ICU.

370
00:19:42,567 --> 00:19:43,700
I was so scared.

371
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:49,133
Please listen to your dad.

372
00:19:49,267 --> 00:19:52,967
Wake up, please wake up.

373
00:20:15,133 --> 00:20:17,467
<i> Acting like a wife, really?</i>

374
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:20,433
<i>You're even accompanying him
to the restroom?</i>

375
00:20:20,567 --> 00:20:22,367
<i> That's my job!</i>

376
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:23,400
<i> I'm the wife!</i>

377
00:20:28,167 --> 00:20:30,800
Miss Ruiz, where is Mr. Cruz?

378
00:20:30,933 --> 00:20:32,400
He's in the restroom.

379
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:37,700
- Doctor.
- Sir.

380
00:20:37,833 --> 00:20:40,767
Sir, we already
alerted security.

381
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:44,300
We've also forwarded
Mrs. Cruz's photo to them.

382
00:20:44,433 --> 00:20:48,100
If she comes back,
they won't let her in.

383
00:20:48,233 --> 00:20:51,500
But, Sir, this might be
the last time

384
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:53,900
we can honor your request.

385
00:20:54,033 --> 00:20:56,600
To be honest, the hospital
could get in trouble

386
00:20:56,733 --> 00:20:59,333
if we impose a total ban on her.

387
00:20:59,467 --> 00:21:01,533
She's still the
patient's mother,

388
00:21:01,667 --> 00:21:04,433
she has the legal rights
to be with her daughter.

389
00:21:04,567 --> 00:21:07,500
Felma and I have
already talked, Doctor.

390
00:21:07,633 --> 00:21:11,367
We're filing a restraining
order against Hazel.

391
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:14,033
<i> You can't stop me, Manuel.</i>

392
00:21:14,167 --> 00:21:16,500
<i>I will find a way
to see my daughter.</i>

393
00:21:54,833 --> 00:21:55,867
Hello?

394
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:59,467
Expect a call from HR, okay?

395
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:02,133
You're about to start
your job here at Southcrest.

396
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:05,767
Oh, really?

397
00:22:05,900 --> 00:22:07,367
Thank you.

398
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:09,967
Why do you sound like
you're not excited?

399
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:11,567
Is something wrong?

400
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:13,500
No, it's nothing.

401
00:22:13,633 --> 00:22:15,133
I'm okay, I got this.

402
00:22:15,300 --> 00:22:16,633
Of course, you do!

403
00:22:16,767 --> 00:22:18,467
You got this, you're an expert.

404
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:25,833
Hello?

405
00:22:25,967 --> 00:22:28,333
You seem so serious.

406
00:22:28,467 --> 00:22:30,300
Okay, do what you
have to do first.

407
00:22:30,433 --> 00:22:31,567
I will see you there.

408
00:22:58,167 --> 00:23:01,067
<i>Jessica, sweetie,
mommy's coming.</i>

409
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:14,367
Manuel?

410
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:16,467
Manuel, you should
get some rest.

411
00:23:18,667 --> 00:23:21,000
I got Jessica a private room

412
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:24,467
so she can transfer there
once she wakes up.

413
00:23:24,633 --> 00:23:26,700
If you want, you can stay there
for now.

414
00:23:26,833 --> 00:23:28,100
Oh, I'm okay. I'll stay here.

415
00:23:29,833 --> 00:23:31,133
But you haven't slept yet.

416
00:23:34,933 --> 00:23:38,100
You've been sitting in
that wheelchair all night.

417
00:23:38,233 --> 00:23:41,933
You have to stretch
your back and your legs.

418
00:23:47,733 --> 00:23:48,467
You know...

419
00:23:51,533 --> 00:23:55,733
When Andrea was in the ICU
before,

420
00:23:55,900 --> 00:23:58,000
I didn't go home either.

421
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:01,667
I didn't get any sleep.

422
00:24:08,567 --> 00:24:11,300
Paz told Abel about that.

423
00:24:11,433 --> 00:24:12,567
She said you were
practically living

424
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,733
at the hospital back then.

425
00:24:14,867 --> 00:24:17,233
You didn't leave her side
until she was all better.

426
00:24:17,367 --> 00:24:19,167
While I was far away.

427
00:24:20,733 --> 00:24:22,767
I was with Hazel.

428
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,600
<i> You two have no shame,</i>

429
00:24:24,733 --> 00:24:25,967
<i>flirting right here,
of all places.</i>

430
00:24:29,033 --> 00:24:30,833
I'm sorry, Felma.

431
00:24:30,967 --> 00:24:34,500
I wasn't there for you before.

432
00:24:34,633 --> 00:24:35,800
Don't worry about that anymore.

433
00:24:35,933 --> 00:24:37,600
It's all in the past now.

434
00:24:37,733 --> 00:24:39,633
And even though you're away,

435
00:24:39,767 --> 00:24:44,700
the money you sent me
saved our daughter's life.

436
00:25:25,767 --> 00:25:26,967
Thank God.

437
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:29,400
Thank you, it's stable.

438
00:25:33,033 --> 00:25:33,900
Sweetie.

439
00:25:43,067 --> 00:25:44,167
Jessica.

440
00:25:51,233 --> 00:25:53,467
Sweetie, please forgive me.

441
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:58,133
Please forgive me,
I didn't mean to hurt you.

442
00:26:04,367 --> 00:26:05,867
Sorry.

443
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,967
Sorry, I'm sorry.

444
00:26:09,133 --> 00:26:10,600
Sorry.

445
00:26:10,733 --> 00:26:12,500
She's drunk,
and you didn't get to score?

446
00:26:12,633 --> 00:26:14,167
Andrea is girlfriend material.

447
00:26:14,300 --> 00:26:16,200
Don't tell me you're
going to pursue her?

448
00:26:16,333 --> 00:26:17,967
She woke up because
she heard my voice!

449
00:26:18,100 --> 00:26:19,067
Let me get back in there!

450
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,000
Hazel, you have to leave!

451
00:26:20,133 --> 00:26:21,767
Please, stop!

452
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:23,600
- How is your job interview?
- They didn't hire me.

453
00:26:23,733 --> 00:26:24,600
There are still many jobs
out there

454
00:26:24,733 --> 00:26:26,200
that don't require a diploma.

455
00:26:26,333 --> 00:26:27,200
Construction worker.

456
00:26:27,333 --> 00:26:28,400
That's a hard job, I'm not used
to doing that.

457
00:26:28,533 --> 00:26:30,833
Yes. I got it.

458
00:26:30,967 --> 00:26:32,267
You might get caught.

459
00:26:32,400 --> 00:26:33,833
Do you think I'll let myself
get caught?
